<item>
            <title>[CASSANDRA-2490] DatabaseDescriptor.defsVersion should be volatile</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CASSANDRA-2490</link>
                <project id="12310865" key="CASSANDRA">Apache Cassandra</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;(Probably affects other versions, but I am on 0.7.3).&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;DatabaseDescriptor.defsVersion should be protected by volatile since it is written to and read by multiple threads from unsynchronized methods. This can manifest itself in schema agreement never occurring due to a node broadcasting the wrong schema version.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
